@gthall1 Agree w @fundatoris all depends on the agreement you have w the advisor. Weekly contribution, monthly and touch what pieces of biz
6/ PPS I try to notify others of angels that lower their investment amount based on advisory negotiations b/c this is bullshit.
5/ PS I have given advisory stock to people who both earned it and those who didn't. Not knocking the overall practice.
4/ Finally, if an angel lowers their investment amount as you negotiate advisory shares, run for the hills.
3/ If you're going to do it, make sure their roles are clearly defined same as you would do with any employee and you hold them accountable
2/ Angels that require advisory stock that aren't contributing tangible value are just asking for lower price and can piss off others.
1/ Pro tip to entrepreneurs raising a seed round. Be very careful of angels that require advisory stock.
